Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a #medium pot{} with a
#tight-fitting lid{}. Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve
(the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and slice
into thin strips.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced).

Zest the @lime{1}(zested). Cut half into wedges and squeeze the rest.

Chop the @tomato{2}(chopped) into small pieces.

Season the @Irish beef rump{250%g} with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and
half the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment
after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Add pepper, half the onion and remaining Mexican spice mix to a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until tender, ~{13-16%minutes}.

In a #bowl{}, mix together the tomato and remaining onion.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and a drizzle of oil.

Meanwhile, place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the beef until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for
medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you like it medium and a further
~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover and allow to rest.

Add @lime juice{1%tsp}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (double both for 4p),
@creme fraiche{65%g} and half the lime zest to a small bowl.

Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Thinly slice the beef.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then stir in the remaining lime zest.

Divide the rice and roast veg between #bowls{}.

Top with the sliced beef rump.

Dollop lime sauce over everything and spoon over the tomato onion salsa.

Squeeze over a lime wedge, if desired.